text:
The peanut butter filling impressed me - i could taste normal butter (or margarine) sugar as well as peanutsss. However it's overall pretty oily and wet (from melted butter i presume).

Bought taro and signature coconut for my family too, total $4.80. Family said the coconut was nice, but taro was too sweet.

Maybe I'm used to QQ kueh texture of Munchi Pancakes so i found this kueh less chewy!
A MJK that is thick and substantial. It is more solid than other out there, not a bad thing if you like it. The flavours and fillings are welcomed such as Matcha, Taro, Black Sesame!!

Tried the matcha and chocolate banana flavors. The pancake flavors were definitely unique but slices were much smaller than what you get from elsewhere. Matcha was decent but the chocolate banana was a bit too sweet for me.

Traditional Food in a Creative Way.

Offers a Variety of Flavors.

Nice and Courteous Bosses ...

Nice pancakes, lots of flavours to choose from!!
Local snack that anyone should come and try
